  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"jump-content\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n            \n\n    \n    \n\n    \u003carticle\u003e\n\n    \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n    \n      \n\n\u003cdiv data-analytics-module=\"{\n    \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Hero Menu\u0026#34;,\n    \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Android Earthquake Alerts now available across the U.S.\u0026#34;\n  }\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003cdiv\u003e\n          \u003cp\u003eSep 03, 2024\u003c/p\u003e\n          \n            \u003cp data-reading-time-render=\"\"\u003e[[read-time]] min read\u003c/p\u003e\n          \n        \u003c/div\u003e\n      \n        \u003cp\u003e\n          With Android, we\u0026#39;re able to send early earthquake warnings — no matter where you are in the U.S.\n        \u003c/p\u003e\n      \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv data-component=\"uni-ai-generated-summary\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n    \u0026#34;event\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;module_impression\u0026#34;,\n    \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;ai_summary\u0026#34;,\n    \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;CTA\u0026#34;\n  }\"\u003e\n      \n        \u003cdiv data-summary-id=\"ai_summary_1\"\u003e\n          \u003ch2\u003eGeneral summary\u003c/h2\u003e\n          \u003cp\u003eAndroid Earthquake Alerts, a life-saving tool that provides early warnings before shaking starts, is now available across all 50 U.S. states and 6 U.S. territories. The system uses accelerometers in Android phones to detect vibrations and crowdsourced data to determine the severity of an earthquake. Two types of alerts, \u0026#34;Be Aware\u0026#34; and \u0026#34;Take Action,\u0026#34; will be sent to phones, and tips on what to do after an earthquake can be found on Google Search.\u003c/p\u003e\n          \n          \u003cp\u003e\u003csmall\u003e\n            Summaries were generated by Google AI. Generative AI is experimental.\n          \u003c/small\u003e\n        \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n      \n        \u003cdiv data-summary-id=\"ai_summary_2\"\u003e\n          \u003ch2\u003eBullet points\u003c/h2\u003e\n          \u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAndroid Earthquake Alerts now available across all 50 U.S. states and 6 U.S. territories.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSystem uses built-in accelerometers in Android phones to detect earthquakes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTwo types of alerts: \u0026#34;Be Aware\u0026#34; and \u0026#34;Take Action\u0026#34;.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTap for tips on what to do after an earthquake.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAndroid Earthquake Alerts System continuously improving through collaboration with experts.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n          \n          \u003cp\u003e\u003csmall\u003e\n            Summaries were generated by Google AI. Generative AI is experimental.\n          \u003c/small\u003e\n        \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n      \n\n      \n      \u003cdiv\u003e\n        \u003ch4\u003e\n          Explore other styles:\n        \u003c/h4\u003e\n        \n      \u003c/div\u003e\n      \n\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \n\n    \n      \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cfigure\u003e\n      \u003cdiv\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg srcset=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/android_earthquake_alerts_hero_1.width-600.format-webp.webp 600w, https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/android_earthquake_alerts_hero_1.width-1200.format-webp.webp 1200w, https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/android_earthquake_alerts_hero_1.width-1600.format-webp.webp 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 599px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 600px, 1024px\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/android_earthquake_alerts_hero_1.width-1200.format-webp.webp\" fetchpriority=\"high\" alt=\"An illustration of an Android earthquake alert that says drop, cover, hold\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n    \n\n    \n    \u003cdiv data-reading-time=\"true\" data-component=\"uni-drop-cap|uni-tombstone\"\u003e\n\n            \n              \n\n\n\u003cgoogle-read-aloud-player data-analytics-module=\"{\n        \u0026#34;event\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;module_impression\u0026#34;,\n        \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;ai_audio\u0026#34;,\n        \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Android Earthquake Alerts now available across the U.S.\u0026#34;\n    }\" data-date-modified=\"2024-09-04T15:52:13.508655+00:00\" data-progress-bar-style=\"half-wave\" data-api-key=\"AIzaSyBLT6VkYe-x7sWLZI2Ep26-fNkBKgND-Ac\" data-article-style=\"style9\" data-tracking-ids=\"G-HGNBTNCHCQ,G-6NKTLKV14N\" data-voice-list=\"en.ioh-pngnat:Cyan,en.usb-pngnat:Lime\" data-layout-style=\"style1\" data-highlight-mode=\"word-over-paragraph\" data-highlight-text-color=\"#000000\" data-highlight-word-background=\"#8AB4F8\" data-highlight-paragraph-background=\"#D2E3FC\" data-background=\"linear-gradient(180deg, #F1F3F4 0%, #F8F9FA 100%)\" data-foreground-color=\"#202124\" data-font=\"600 16px Google Sans, sans-serif\" data-box-shadow=\"0px 1px 3px 1px rgba(60, 64, 67, 0.15)\"\u003e\n\u003c/google-read-aloud-player\u003e\n\n\n\n\n            \n\n            \n            \n\n\n  \n    \u003cdiv data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Paragraph\u0026#34;,\n           \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Android Earthquake Alerts now available across the U.S.\u0026#34;\n         }\"\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"hco1h\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.android.com/safety/physical-safety/\"\u003eSafety alerts\u003c/a\u003e play a crucial role in helping people prepare for natural disasters and emergencies. This is especially true for earthquakes, where early warnings can make all the difference. To help millions of Android users stay safe, the Android Earthquake Alerts System can provide early warnings seconds before shaking starts. Starting today, we’re expanding the system to cover all 50 U.S. states and 6 U.S. territories. The rollout will be completed over the coming weeks.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 data-block-key=\"cvr2j\"\u003eHow Android Earthquake Alerts work in the U.S.\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"sldn\"\u003eSince 2020, we\u0026#39;ve partnered with the United States Geological Survey (USGS), California Governor\u0026#39;s Office of Emergency Services (CalOES) and the ShakeAlert® system to make Android Earthquake Alerts available in California, Oregon and Washington. These alerts rely on traditional seismometers to detect earthquakes. To supplement these existing government earthquake alert systems and bring early warnings to places that do not have USGS ShakeAlert®, this expansion uses the built-in accelerometers in Android phones to bring another layer of preparedness and potentially life-saving information to people across every state.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n  \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n      \u003cdiv data-analytics-module=\"{\n          \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Inline Images\u0026#34;,\n          \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Android Earthquake Alerts now available across the U.S.\u0026#34;\n        }\"\u003e\n  \n\n  \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A map of the U.S. that shows that Android Earthquake Alerts are available in all 50 states and six territories\" src=\" https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Earthquake_Alerts_Map.width-100.format-webp.webp \" loading=\"lazy\" data-loading=\"{\n                \u0026#34;mobile\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Earthquake_Alerts_Map.width-500.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;,\n                \u0026#34;desktop\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Earthquake_Alerts_Map.width-1000.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;\n              }\"/\u003e\n        \n      \n    \n    \u003c/p\u003e\n    \n  \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\n\n  \n\n  \n    \u003cdiv data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Paragraph\u0026#34;,\n           \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Android Earthquake Alerts now available across the U.S.\u0026#34;\n         }\"\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"hco1h\"\u003eThese accelerometers can sense vibrations, which indicate that an earthquake may be happening. When phones in an area detect shaking, the \u003ca href=\"https://crisisresponse.google/android-alerts/\"\u003eAndroid Earthquake Alerts System\u003c/a\u003e analyzes the crowdsourced data to determine if an earthquake is occurring. This technology is already being used to deliver alerts in \u003ca href=\"https://support.google.com/android/answer/9319337?hl=en#zippy=%2Cget-alerts-for-nearby-earthquakes:~:text=Where%20the%20Android%20Earthquake%20Alerts%20System%20is%20active\"\u003e97 other countries\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"9a2st\"\u003eIf an earthquake of magnitude 4.5 or greater is detected, two types of warning alerts will be sent to your phone:\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli data-block-key=\"bckkg\"\u003e\u0026#34;Be Aware\u0026#34; Alert: This alert signals weak or light shaking, giving you a heads-up to prepare for potential stronger shaking.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli data-block-key=\"b5ti4\"\u003e\u0026#34;Take Action\u0026#34; Alert: This alert indicates that moderate to extreme shaking is expected, and prompts you to take immediate action to protect yourself.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n  \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n      \u003cdiv data-analytics-module=\"{\n          \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Inline Images\u0026#34;,\n          \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Android Earthquake Alerts now available across the U.S.\u0026#34;\n        }\"\u003e\n  \n\n  \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Image of the two different types of Android earthquake alerts\" src=\" https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Android-Earthquake-Alerts_Update.width-100.format-webp.webp \" loading=\"lazy\" data-loading=\"{\n                \u0026#34;mobile\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Android-Earthquake-Alerts_Update.width-500.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;,\n                \u0026#34;desktop\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Android-Earthquake-Alerts_Update.width-1000.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;\n              }\"/\u003e\n        \n      \n    \n    \u003c/p\u003e\n    \n  \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\n\n  \n\n  \n    \u003cdiv data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Paragraph\u0026#34;,\n           \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Android Earthquake Alerts now available across the U.S.\u0026#34;\n         }\"\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"hco1h\"\u003eOnce the shaking is over, you can tap for tips on what to do next. You can also see earthquake information from Android Earthquake Alerts in Google Search – simply search for “Earthquake near me”.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 data-block-key=\"2p20d\"\u003eCollaboration for continuous improvement\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"998v8\"\u003eWe\u0026#39;ve collaborated with renowned seismologists like Dr. Lucy Jones, dedicated academic researchers like Dr. Jeannette Sutton, and disaster response organizations like the Global Disaster Preparedness Center (GDPC) to inform and improve Android Earthquake Alerts. Actively engaging with experts in the field and analyzing data after detected seismic events allows us to continuously improve the Android Earthquake Alerts System.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 data-block-key=\"3bgc5\"\u003eStay safe with Android\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"6p70l\"\u003eYour safety is our priority, and we are continuously working to provide you with the tools and information you need to stay prepared during emergencies. We remain dedicated to collaborating with the earthquake community, emergency managers and device manufacturers to further advance earthquake alerts and response efforts.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"8fsn7\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://support.google.com/android/answer/9319337?hl=en\"\u003eLearn more\u003c/a\u003e about supported countries and how to enable Android Earthquake Alerts compatible devices. Keep a lookout for more information about the science and technology behind the Android Earthquake Alerts System in an upcoming paper.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n  \n    \n\n\u003csection data-analytics-module=\"{\n  \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Related Content Tout\u0026#34;,\n  \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;5 new Android features\u0026#34;\n}\"\u003e\n  \u003ca href=\"https://blog.google/products/android/new-android-features-september-2024/\" data-ga4-analytics-cta-click=\"{\n  \u0026#34;event\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;cta_click\u0026#34;,\n  \u0026#34;link_text\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;See more\u0026#34;\n}\" data-ga4-analytics-lead-click=\"{\n  \u0026#34;event\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;article_lead_click\u0026#34;,\n  \u0026#34;link_text\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;5 new Android features to help you explore, search for music and more\u0026#34;,\n  \u0026#34;link_type\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;internal\u0026#34;,\n  \u0026#34;article_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;5 new Android features to help you explore, search for music and more\u0026#34;,\n  \u0026#34;author_name\u0026#34; : \u0026#34;Angana Ghosh\u0026#34;,\n  \u0026#34;page_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;new-android-features-september-2024\u0026#34;,\n  \u0026#34;position\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;1 of 1\u0026#34;,\n  \u0026#34;c